This submodule focuses on the dynamics of household and government consumption within the economy. It captures the total expenditures made by households (Household_Consumption), government entities (Government_Expenditure), and non-profit institutions serving households (NPISH). By integrating these components, the module calculates Final Consumption, which is a critical driver of GDP. The submodule also examines the relationship between consumption, income distribution, and macroeconomic variables, allowing for scenario-based projections that reflect changing consumption patterns over time. It provides insights into how shifts in income, fiscal policy, and external factors influence overall consumption, thus impacting economic growth and stability.
