10,33,ECONOMY ENERGY SCARCITY,1603,519,1277,61,3,3,0,31,-1,0,0,0,0-128-0,0-64-0,|72|B|255-255-128,0,0,0,0,0,0
12,34,0,1650,682,1035,44,8,7,0,8,-1,0,0,0,-1--1--1,-1--1--1,|24||0-0-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
This submodule focuses on the dynamics of energy availability and demand within the economic model. It quantifies how the limited availability of energy resources affects production capabilities and consumption patterns across various sectors, including industry, transportation, and households. The submodule calculates the Energy_Scarcity_Indicator by comparing total available energy supply to projected energy demand, expressed as a ratio between 0 and 1. This indicator provides insights into the adequacy of energy resources to meet economic needs. By integrating data on energy consumption, production activities, and resource availability, the submodule allows for scenario analysis that explores the impacts of varying energy conditions on economic performance and sustainability. Understanding energy scarcity is critical for evaluating how constraints on energy resources can influence overall economic growth and the ability to transition to more sustainable energy practices.
